14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 57 O.S. 2021, Section 332.1B, is
16 amended to read as follows:
17 Section 332.1B. A. To be eligible for appointment as a Pardon
18 and Parole Board member, a As provided in Section 10, Article VI of
19 the Oklahoma Constitution, the Governor shall appoint three of the
20 five members of the Pardon and Parole Board, the Chief Justice of
21 the Supreme Court shall appoint one member, and the presiding judge
22 of the Criminal Court of Appeals shall appoint one member. In
23 addition to the requirements provided for in subsections B, C, and D
24 of this section, each person appointed shall possess a bachelor's
