11 9. 11. Social work.
12 B. At least two members of the Pardon and Parole Board 1. One
13 member appointed by the Governor shall have a minimum of five (5)
14 years of training or experience in mental health services, substance
15 abuse services or social work.;
16 2. One member appointed by the Governor shall have a minimum of
17 five (5) years of experience as a former correctional officer; and
18 3. One member appointed by the Governor shall have a minimum of
19 five (5) years of experience as a former district attorney or
20 assistant district attorney.
21 C. One member appointed by the Chief Justice of the Supreme
22 Court shall be a former district court judge with a minimum of five
23 (5) years of experience presiding over a criminal court docket.
